The Minister of Labour and Employment, Dr. Chris Ngige, yesterday, inaugurated the newly appointed board members of the Nigerian Social Insurance Trust Fund (NSITF) after a two-year delay under the chairmanship of Prince Austin Enajemo-Isire. Other board members are Mrs. Ijeoma Oji Okoronkwo (board secretary), Olawale Osuolale Timothy (NECA), Dr. Mohammed J. Yinusa (NECA), Com. Waheed Adewale Adeyanju (NLC), Com. Ibrahim Khaleel (NLC), Ifeoma Anyawutaku (Federal Ministry of Labour and Employment) and Mrs. Umma Aminu (CBN). Others are Jasper Azutalam (Executive Director Finance and Investment), Tijani Suleiman Darazo (Executive Director Administration), Titilola Olukemi Nelson (Executive Director Operations), Adedayo K. Somefun (Managing Director/Chief Executive). BREAKING: Presidency resolves NSITF tussle, appoints Kokori as Michael Imoudu board's chair Ngige inaugurates NSITF board, Kokori redeployed to institute NSITF board chair: NLC, NUPENG against Kokori’s substitution Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin